Each refrigeration system has an emergency control box which can be used in an emergency situation to equalize the pressures between the low side and the high side, or to manually diffuse ammonia through the ammonia/water diffuser.



Accidental Release Prevention Program



Woodbridge Winery has developed an accidental release prevention program for compliance with the EPA RMP and OES CalARP regulations.  The program includes but is not limited to the following elements:

?    Process safety information regarding the hazards of ammonia, and operating and technical specifications for the refrigeration systems and the associated equipment;

?    Written procedures for operating and maintaining the refrigeration systems;

?    Training for personnel involved with system operations and maintenance;

?    Written procedures for safely introducing modifications to the processes;

?    Investigating releases of ammonia and near miss incidents and implementing measures to prevent recurrence; 

?    Written procedures for conducting hot work on or near the processes;

?    Contractor management policies to ensure contract employee safety while on facility premises;

?    Audit procedures for ensuring that the programs are being implemented in accordance to the regulations; and

?    Employee involvement in program development and implementation.



In addition, engineering controls have been implemented to reduce the chance of an accidental release to the environment.  These are comprised of equipment monitoring systems and safety controls to shut off the equipment when operating parameters exceed safe operating limits.  Relief valves on pressurized ammonia vessels prevent equipment rupture in the event of overpressurization.  Regular inspections and tests are performed to ensure these controls are in good working order.



